    <TD height="44" width="594" colspan="2">
<p align="center"><STRONG style="font-weight: 400"><FONT size=4 face="Arial"> 
Chronobot &amp; Virtual Classroom (CVC) System</FONT></STRONG></TD>
        </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD width="594" colspan="2">
<P align=justify>&nbsp;</P>
<P align=justify><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><b><i>Virtual Classroom</i></b> 
is a simulated classroom via Internet, which provides a convenient&nbsp; 
communication environment for distance learners just&nbsp; like traditional 
face-to-face style classroom. However, it is not a simply duplicated classroom 
from real life to virtual space. Some unique features such as information 
fusion, user's profiling and evolutionary interface are being incorporated.  The tool can run on the PC or in virtual PC on the Mac.</span></P>
<P align=justify><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">A <i><b>Chronobot</b></i> is a 
device for storing and borrowing time. Using the Chronobot one can borrow time 
from someone else and/or return time to the same person. It is a very convenient 
device for managing time.</span></P>
<P align=justify><FONT face="Arial"> <STRONG><i>Chronobot 
&amp; Virtual Classroom</i></STRONG><STRONG style="font-weight: 400"> (CVC) System is an integration of Chronobot and Virtual 
Classroom. It allows users freely switch between these two applications and get 
maximum benefit from both.</STRONG></FONT></P>
<P align=justify>&nbsp;</P></TD>
        </TR>
